IN THE HIGH COURT OF PUNJAB AND HARYANA AT
CHANDIGARH

C.W.P. No. 2746 of 1984 
Date of decision: 19.11.2010
Captain Shamsher Singh
..............Petitioner
Versus
The Indian Red Cross Society & Others 
................Respondents
CORAM:- HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE RANJAN GOGOI
Present:
None
RANJAN GOGOI,J.(oral)
This writ petition has been filed inter alia with the following
prayer:-
  to issue a writ of certiorari quashing the impugned
nomination of respondents No.4 to 12 as members of the
Managing Body vide Notification dated 22nd May, 1984
(Annexure P-5) 
By notification dated 22.5.1984 (Annexure P-5) respondents
Nos.4 to 12 have been nominated as members of the Chandigarh U.T.Red
Cross Branch for a period of one year from the date of notification dated
.5.1984. The writ petition, therefore has become infructuous. It is,
therefore, closed as infructuous. 
(RANJAN GOGOI)
JUDGE
November 19, 2010
